t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As our plane de=
scended toward the Black Mountain, we saw the glowing Adriatic Sea in the d=
istance. Night fell. We weaved our way along narrow mountain roads and ente=
red a deep tunnel, emerging on the other side of an otherwise impassible ro=
ck face. Our ride ended at a small beach village nestled directly at the fo=
ot of the mountains. It was not an </span><em>ordinary</em><span> beach vil=
lage. This was a city within a city, an experiment with statehood embedded =
within another state. Members of a global digital tribe concerned with runn=
ing one of the largest World Computers had decided to make this their tempo=
rary home for several months. It was an experiment in digital citizenship.<=
/span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>We joined this city as representatives of another=
 tribe&#8212;the biotic tribe. In their ongoing experiment with statehood, =
the World Computer tribe had come to a realization. </span><strong>Sovereig=
nty is intimately connected to physical abundance</strong><span>. Societies=
 need to run on atoms. Materials, food, water, medicines. They began to won=
der: what tools exist to develop local, independent, sustainable supply cha=
ins? Our answer was: </span><strong>biology</strong><span>. Using the tools=
 of </span><em>synthetic biology</em><span>, perhaps this new Network State=
 could one day meet all of its material needs by </span><em>growing everyth=
ing</em><span>. Could they </span><em>grow</em><span> their own cement to m=
ake new buildings, their clothing, and their medicines by using biology as =
a technology?</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>This was a Summit&#8212;a meeting=
 between tribes. It was a chance to establish a shared language. To conside=
r how distributed biomanufacturing could advance the cause of Network State=
s, and how the vast and decentralized World Computer could be harnessed to =
accelerate science.</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>No, unlike Packy&#8217;s </=
span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/3d654a39-7312-4043-bef2-390cd=
4d2b55b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU"=
 rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">recent story</a>=
<span>, this is not a piece of science fiction. I&#8217;m describing my rec=
ent trip to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/194770af-860c-4=
0e7-aa8d-5acd0bf2d027?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Zu=
zalu</a><span>, a pop-up city located in Montenegro, for the </span><a href=
=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/d32b82b3-41eb-4308-97f7-73a018cace94?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=
=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Blockchain Meets Bio Summi=
t</a><span>. This workshop was held between leaders in the blockchain and s=
ynthetic biology communities to identify fruitful points of connection and =
collaboration. When I heard this was happening, I knew that Packy and I nee=
ded to go. Packy has spent a lot of time thinking really hard about the wil=
d world of web3, and I&#8217;ve done the same for synthetic biology&#8212;t=
wo core focus areas of Not Boring were colliding! Ironically, while Zuzalu =
is experimenting with developing </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/aab8e71b-3d2f-493a-acb5-30bae32c4030?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decor=
ation: underline;">frictionless digital passports using zero-knowledge proo=
fs</a><span>, Packy wasn&#8217;t able to make the trip because of the diffi=
culty involved in updating his U.S. passport. So, you&#8217;re getting my r=
endition of the events&#8212;and of the key ideas discussed at this summit.=
</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As the resident bio-optimist at Not Boring, I was exci=
ted to brainstorm about ways to power future societies using distributed bi=
omanufacturing. Beyond that, a major goal in attending this summit was to m=
ore deeply understand the other direction of this relationship&#8212;what p=
roblems are members of the Decentralized Science (DeSci) community solving =
for scientists? While sentiment around crypto is at a major low, the DeSci =
community seems to remain as energized as ever.</p><p style=3D"color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Zuzalu h=
as been </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/46a11a83-f760-4a66-=
