e IP and commercialize the new technology as a product. This is the current=
 status quo, but the process has real inefficiencies and most IP remains do=
rmant. </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7bd39af7-6b49-4205-a=
f7a-3040008836c7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m=
8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Paul Ko=
hlhaas</a><span>, the co-founder and CEO of Molecule, wondered &#8220;</spa=
n><strong>What if instead of using NFTs for trading pictures of monkeys, we=
 used them to solve a real problem like creating a more fluid IP marketplac=
e?</strong><span>&#8221;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The core IP-NFT protocol=
 is a complicated piece of legal and technical innovation, so it&#8217;s ea=
sier to get an intuition for the use case by focusing on how early projects=
 have been structured. The </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/=
1af6439e-f1e7-44ad-9ecf-4992f0792a78?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration:=
 underline;">Scheibye-Knudsen Group</a><span> at the University of Copenhag=
en ran a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/04c0220d-f115-47fb=
-bb28-800c564bf0d9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">large=
-scale analysis of the impact of prescription drugs on survival</a><span> u=
sing a dataset of 1.5 billion prescriptions from 4.8 million individuals ov=
er 40 years in The Danish National Health Service Prescription Database. Th=
ey identified a set of over ten drugs correlated with extended human lifesp=
an. Then, they minted this finding </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/r=
edirect/dcb45738-c1c1-4c50-a0ff-e284299a6a94?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-dec=
oration: underline;">as an IP-NFT</a><span> using the Molecule protocol, wh=
ich was then transferred to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect=
/d7059ea2-33d1-466b-91a4-5c50a6779fc1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration=
: underline;">VitaDAO</a><span>&#8212;a web3 community focused on funding l=
ongevity research. This transaction will fund a new study focused &#8220;on=
 optimizing, repurposing, and re-formulating the 3 drugs with the strongest=
 effect on human lifespan.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #40404=
0; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And who i=
s funding VitaDAO? Somewhat surprisingly, venture capitalists and even Big =
Pharma have been willing to interact with this community very early on. Vit=
aDAO announced a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/23f223c7-7=
325-4660-8139-65c80d00e1c9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline=
;">strategic $4.1M </a><span>fundraising that placed Pfizer Ventures alongs=
ide Shine Capital, L1 Digital, and Balaji Srinivasan. These extremely diver=
se funders are making a bet that protocols like IP-NFTs and research commun=
ities like VitaDAO will succeed in establishing a new funding marketplace f=
or high-quality early-stage biomedical research. </span><strong>In our life=
time, will the IP for a blockbuster drug be financed on the blockchain?</st=
rong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Intellectual property still exists in the realm of=
 bits, but crypto is beginning to infiltrate the world of atoms, too An org=
anization called </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/4bb3d23f-b=
115-4892-a095-98cec7029c2c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline=
;">LabDAO</a><span> is working to build &#8220;</span><strong>the science e=
xecution layer for Biotech DAOs.</strong><span>&#8221; This community is bu=
ilding a lab marketplace and set of computational tools to help these decen=
tralized digital communities carry out their research.</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>Here&#8217;s the </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/8f=
5f33e3-c32e-41b8-9a40-d3de789f32d6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: u=
nderline;">main idea</a><span>:</span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left:=
 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: #404040=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px=
;"><em>LabDAO members build data and resource management software, in retur=
n for token ownership. The DAO interacts with physical labs (existing or ne=
w) by paying to run experiments and providing data or materials to the toke=
n holders who funded the work. Data can be managed in an electronic lab not=
ebook (ELN) on chain, using NFT datasets, for later licensing or use by thi=
rd parties. New labs can join the DAO to earn tokens for their services or =
to support scientific progress by providing their methods at cost.</em></p>=
<p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Start with simple, easily outsourced proje=
cts - &#8220;bit to bit&#8221; projects requiring the user to supply data t=
o be analyzed (e.g. bioinformatics or screening experiments) and receiving =
data out the other side. Then move to &#8220;bit to atom&#8221; and &#8220;=
atom to atom&#8221; projects.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>They are=
 trying to use the World Computer to increase fluidity between bits and ato=
ms. With infrastructure like the IP-NFT protocol and LabDAO in place, more =
science DAOs are starting to emerge. </span><strong>The range of interests =
is substantial, which is sort of the point</strong><span>. Looking through =
the DAOs on </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/2d44a1b2-06ba-4=
712-ac30-6770424c5fe1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">bi=
o.xyz</a><span>&#8212;a biotech DAO accelerator&#8212;the projects range fr=
om </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/d7059ea2-33d1-466b-91a4-=
5c50a6779fc1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">longevity</=
a><span>, to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/628885ed-a8cf-=
4bf6-a9d9-f50f6a107e50?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">s=
ynthetic biology</a><span>, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect=
/1b1bd8fe-083b-4314-8b41-ed1f4c91c0e6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration=
: underline;">women&#8217;s health</a><span>, or </span><a href=3D"https://=
substack.com/redirect/02e1eaf5-ac71-42bd-a673-eee5ff8444ca?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #40=
4040; text-decoration: underline;">even hair loss</a><span>. Yes, hair loss=
=2E</span></p><a href=3D"https://substac=
k.com/redirect/1c60280e-19f9-45d6-af4=
c-174898e39c91?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"youtube-wrap" data-component-name=3D"You=
tube2ToDOMStatic" style=3D"display: block; margin: 1.6em 0;"><img src=3D"ht=
tps://substackcdn.com/image/youtube/w_550,c_limit/l_youtube_play_qyqt8q,w_1=
20/8D3znGl7ukU" style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !imp=
ortant; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 100%; vert=
ical-align: middle; width: 100%;"></a><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It doesn&#8217;t matter wha=
t the project is, the goal is to create a web3 toolbox for communities to m=
obilize around whatever they want to research and to actually make things h=
appen.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">One common question from web3 skeptics is: &#8220=
;Why does this require web3? Why isn&#8217;t HairDAO just HairLLC? We don&#=
8217;t need to reinvent corporate structures and governance.&#8221; After s=
pending some time with various DAO communities at Zuzalu, I care less about=
 this type of skepticism.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Clearly, people from all=
 around the world are deriving value from these new tools for coordination,=
 ownership, and transaction. Increasingly my mental model of web3 is that i=
t is a new set of Web protocols that has the potential to transform all of =
the energy stored up in hyperactive subReddits into actual decentralized co=
mmunities working to solve the problems they care about. </span><strong>The=
 proof of the value of these new tools is the extent to which they catalyze=
 real action</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>At Zuzalu, Paul Kohl=
haas asked the question: &#8220;</span><strong>Statistically, what is the s=
ingle largest determining factor in a person&#8217;s overall success?</stro=
ng><span>&#8221; The answer is: the zip code where you were born. This is e=
specially true for access to science. As a scientist with the privilege of =
working at Stanford, I benefit from great funding resources, high-performan=
ce computing (HPC) resources, one of the best tech-transfer offices, and a =
circling swarm of VCs in the area.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The boldest ve=
rsion of the DeSci vision is to build the Web-native versions of these reso=
urces: better funding mechanisms (IP-NFTs, etc.), better HPC resources and =
lab marketplaces using the World Computer (LabDAO, etc.), better translatio=
nal resources (the growing army of BioDAOs). I was consistently amazed by t=
he diversity of this growing community in terms of both countries of origin=
 and training backgrounds.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If synthetic biology could offer ne=
twork states a new level of physical vitality and abundance, the reciprocal=
 offer from the crypto community is to build the protocols, tools, and comm=
unities to spread access to science to every corner of the globe.</p><div s=
tyle=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0=
e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"></div><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>As somebody embedded in the world of research and startups, I&#8217=
;m comfortable with the idea that our future will be </span><em>very</em><s=
pan> different from the present. Frankly, I&#8217;m an accelerationist. I b=
elieve we should accelerate progress in the physical world and </span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/405e1afb-c0bf-4677-99d9-056178a8c96f?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel styl=
e=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">use biotechnology to expa=
nd life&#8217;s presence in the universe</a><span>. Still, my weekend at Zu=
zalu updated my priors on just how weird and different the future might be.=
</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Outside of the nation-states that most of us inhabit, =
technologists are attempting to build totally new sovereignties. These netw=
ork states and startup cities will be the home to new types of political an=
d physical experimentation&#8212;and they may be some of the earliest adopt=
ers of our most advanced distributed biomanufacturing solutions.</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Just as scientists have solutions to offer to network states, DeSci is w=
orking to give anybody with an Internet connection the ability to participa=
te in cutting-edge research. Perhaps crypto is &#8220;seeding a parallel un=
iverse with online communities&#8221; but these communities hold the ideals=
 of permissionless entrance and community ownership. I, for one, will be fo=
llowing their progress&#8212;waiting to see the first moment where a medici=
ne funded by a DAO delivers value in the clinic. What a time to be alive!</=
p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><span>Departing from the </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com=
/redirect/d32b82b3-41eb-4308-97f7-73a018cace94?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5=
T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-d=
ecoration: underline;">Blockchain Meets Bio Summit</a><span>, I had a conne=
cting flight through Istanbul, Turkey. As we flew into the city, the </span=
><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/c8023187-f6df-418f-8b24-15fdc31ce=
936?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=
 style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Bosporus Strait</a><=
span> was visible out of the window. This incredibly narrow waterway forms =
part of the continental boundary between Asia and Europe. Walking around Is=
tanbul, there is a palpable sense of being situated between bordering cultu=
res. Swarming bazaars sell Turkish delights and spices next to enormous Ori=
ental lamps. The walls of ancient mosques are decorated with Christian mura=
ls&#8212;a direct repercussion of the Crusades. Intersections are rich, vib=
rant, and complicated places. It&#8217;s still uncertain what will happen a=
t the intersection of crypto and biology, but new threads and communities a=
re being woven together. It&#8217;s probably worth assuming that the future=
 will be </span><em>way</em><span> </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/r=
edirect/abbf3078-d690-485b-aaf6-0d38eb85968d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-dec=
oration: underline;">crazier than the present</a><span>.</span></p><div sty=
